# Task 1: Business Logic Layer - Class Diagram

## Overview

This document presents the detailed class diagram of
the Business Logic Layer for the HBnB Evolution application.  
The focus is on the core entities: **User, Place, Review, and Amenity**.  
Each entity is described with its attributes, methods,
and relationships based on the business logic requirements.

-----------------------------------------

## Class Diagram (Mermaid)

```mermaid
classDiagram
class User {
    +UUID id
    +String first_name
    +String last_name
    +String email
    +String password
    +Datetime created_at
    +Datetime updated_at
    +register()
    +update_profile()
}

class Place {
    +UUID id
    +String title
    +String description
    +float price
    +float latitude
    +float longitude
    +UUID owner_id
    +Datetime created_at
    +Datetime updated_at
    +add_amenity()
    +update_info()
}

class Review {
    +UUID id
    +UUID user_id
    +UUID place_id
    +int rating
    +String comment
    +Datetime created_at
    +Datetime updated_at
    +edit_review()
}

class Amenity {
    +UUID id
    +String name
    +String description
    +Datetime created_at
    +Datetime updated_at
}

User "1" --> "0..*" Place : owns >
Place "1" --> "0..*" Review : has >
User "1" --> "0..*" Review : writes >
Place "1" --> "0..*" Amenity : includes >




Explanatory Notes

-User-
Represents a user in the system.

Can be a regular user or an admin.
Registers, logs in, and manages their profile.
Can create places and leave reviews.
-Place-
Represents a property listed by a user.

Includes details like title, description, location, and price.
Linked to the user who owns it.
May contain amenities and receive reviews.
-Review-
Represents feedback left by a user on a place.

Contains a rating and a comment.
Tied to both a user and a place.
-Amenity-
Represents a feature or facility available in a place.

Examples: Wi-Fi, air conditioning, parking.
Linked to one or more places.

--------------------------------------------------------------

 Relationships

User → Place: One user can own multiple places.
User → Review: One user can write many reviews.
Place → Review: One place can receive many reviews.
Place → Amenity: A place can include multiple amenities.

--------------------------------------------------------------

 Summary

This class diagram provides a clear overview of the Business Logic Layer's core entities and their interactions.
It supports modular design and aligns with SOLID principles, ensuring that each class has a focused responsibility and promotes scalable system architecture.
